    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clbeaconregion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object defines a region that you use to detect Bluetooth beacons conforming to the iBeacon specification. Whereas a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clcircularregion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is centered on a geographic location, a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clbeaconregion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is focused on an iBeacon with specific identifying characteristics, which you provide. When a matching device comes in range, Core Location notifies your app."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You monitor beacon regions in two ways. To detect when a beacon is in range, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager/1423656-startmonitoringforregion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method of your location manager object. After detecting a beacon, call the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager/1620554-startrangingbeaconsinregion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method to determine the relative distance to that beacon. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When detecting an iBeacon, you must specify the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clbeaconregion/1621556-proximityuuid"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clbeaconregion/1621536-major"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/clbeaconregion/1621414-minor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
